latestPosts.caption:
Crafts of India campaign for @anitadongre , a brand deeply rooted in celebrating India’s rich craft heritage through design . 

The project celebrates timeless crafts : Bandhani, Ajrakh and Banarasi for a brand that remains India proud and reimagines the exquisite textiles of the subcontinent. 

A heartfelt thank you to our talented team for their unwavering dedication in bringing this vision to life. 

Photography : @anubhav_sood 
Creative direction and styling : @devanshi.15 
Art direction : @harshasinha_ @elementsprodn 
Hair and makeup : @yin.aien @akram_salmani_artist

latestPosts.caption:
This shoot began with a song, onset of early Delhi winters, dreaming up a scene straight out of a movie.

Imagined an intimate musical evening inside a warm, jazz bar — where strangers gather, a band plays, and two lovers and ballroom performers take to the floor,lost in rhythm, and in each other.

Every character was sketched, shaped,styled and shot to play their part.

I wanted it to feel like a moment from a film — where you don’t just see the clothes, you feel the story. 

Thank you to the most wonderful team for bringing this to life . 

Shoot for @originandode .

latestPosts.caption:
My styling philosophy? 

Break the rules, but make it breezy. I took @nicojournal’s pieces for a spin—layered it up, mixed prints with prints, added a clash where you’d least expect it, and somehow making it all feel like second nature.
